net.realmproject.dcm.command

Class CommandDevice<T extends DeviceState>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The data type used to report the state of this device
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    DeviceEventSender
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConnectedCommandDevice, TestAnnotatedCommandDevice, TestAnnotatedCommandDevice

    public abstract class CommandDevice<T extends DeviceState>
extends Device
    Building on top of the Device component, a CommandDevice accepts values of type Command and returns values of type T.

    Methods annotated with the CommandMethod interface will be detected automatically, and commands with an action field matching the method name (or CommandMethod annotation value) will automatically be routed to the corresponding method.

    CommandMethods may accept 0 or 1 arguments. If a method accepts 1 argument, the arguments section of a received command will be converted into the appropriate data type via reflection.
    Author:
    NAS

      • setValue

        public final void setValue(java.lang.Object o)
        Description copied from class: Device
        Sets the value of this device. Users should not expect that a call to setValue(X) followed by a call to getValue() will return X. Due to the nature of physical devices, it may take some time for the device to reach the desired state (if it ever does).

        It is also possible for a device to accept values which act as deltas or commands, in which case the result of getValue should logically match up with the requested action, but may not be an equivalent value or even a similar data structure.
        Specified by:
        setValue in class Device
        Parameters:
        o - The value to set this device to
